text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia catenulata is a tree belonging to the genus Acacia and the subgenus Juliflorae. It is native to an area of the Pilbara region of Western Australia.The tree typically grows to a height of 15 metres (49 ft) with a dark deeply fluted trunk.
text.Taxonomy:
It was first published by C.T.White in 1944.
There are two recognised subspecies

A. c. subsp. catenulata
A. c. subsp. occidentalis
